
How to build on debian:

1: upgrade to squeeze
2: apt-get install build-essential
3: apt-get install pkg-config
4: apt-get install libmemcached-dev
5: apt-get install nodejs-dev
6: git clone git://github.com/vanillahsu/node-memcache.git
7: cd node-memcache; nodejs-waf configure; nodejs-waf
8: nodejs test/test.js
9: done.


How to build on FreeBSD:

1: upgrade your ports tree.
2: cd /usr/ports/database/libmemcached; make install clean;
3: cd /usr/ports/www/node; make install clean;
4: git clone git://github.com/vanillahsu/node-memcache.git
5: cd node-memcache; node-waf configure; node-waf
6: node test/test.js
7: done.
